HEADWORD: Pregravate
<hw>Pre"gra*vate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praegravatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>praegravare</ets> to be heavy
upon, fr. <ets>praegravis</ets> very heavy.]</ety> <def>To bear down; to
depress.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

